    <title>Universal equations for isotropic Grassmannians</title>
    <summary>  The isotropic Grassmannian parametrizes isotropic subspaces of a quadratic
space. In this paper, we show that any maximal isotropic Grassmannian in its
Pl\"ucker embedding can be defined by pulling back the equations of
$Gr_{iso}(3,7)$ or $Gr_{iso}(4,8)$.
</summary>
